Agree.  
It somehow mixing influences from [Caslon Graphique](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/caslon+graphique) [Trooper Roman](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/e-daylight.jp/design/fonts/type/t/trooper-roman.html) and [Bernase Roman](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/e-daylight.jp/design/fonts/type/b/bernase-roman.html). Some interesting ones, far from being even loosely similars actually: [Acta](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/acta) (Display and Poster), [Mafra Display](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/dstype/mafra-display), [Grumpy](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/suomi/grumpy), [Dala Floda](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020021427/http:/commercialtype.com/typefaces/dala_floda)
